If anyone out there is facing the same or similar problem, this is how I did it.
First, I created a recyclerview item click listener interface named **_OnRecyclerViewItemClickListener_** as follows

    import android.view.View;
    public interface OnRecyclerViewItemClickListener {
       void onItemClick(int position, View view);
    }
With this interface we can implement it in an **_Activity_** or **_Fragment_**. This will override the itemclick method in my activity.

Then I added the following into my CategoriesRecyclerViewAdapter.

    ....
    private OnRecyclerViewItemClickListener onRecyclerViewItemClickListener;
    public void setOnRecyclerViewItemClickListener(OnRecyclerViewItemClickListener onRecyclerViewItemClickListener) {
        this.onRecyclerViewItemClickListener = onRecyclerViewItemClickListener;
    }
    ...
Up next, in onBindViewHolder method, I declared the layout setOnclicklistener in this manner.

    ...
    myViewHolder.mCategoryThumbnail.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
            @Override
            public void onClick(View v) {
                if (onRecyclerViewItemClickListener != null) {
                    onRecyclerViewItemClickListener.onItemClick(position, v);
                }
            }
        });
